@node "intro" "Introduction"

@{u}@{b}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

atheros5000.device is a SANA-II network driver for PCI wireless Ethernet
cards based on the Atheros AR5000-series chipset. WEP, WPA and WPA2
encryption are supported, including both TKIP and CCMP (AES) encryption
modes.

The table below shows compatibility information for atheros5000.device with
a variety of wireless cards. However, there are hardware incompatibilities
between some compatible cards and some AmigaOS 4 systems. Cards that only
support the IEEE 802.11a wireless standard have been excluded where known,
since atheros5000.device does not support this mode. Also, cards that
support IEEE 802.11n are unlikely to work.

